Looks like the only issue is that in `setBothFromSI` and `setBothFromUS`, you&#39;re trying to update the variables `siValue` and `usValue`. But nothing is rendering those variables, your inputs are actually rendering the values contained in each `unit`, because of the `{#each units as { usValue, siValue } }` block

So in those `setBoth` functions, you probably want to be updating the values inside of `units`, like this:

```javascript
function setBothFromSI(value, i) {
	const { factor } = units[i];

	units[i].siValue = +value;
	units[i].usValue = +(value / factor).toFixed(2);
}
function setBothFromUS(value, i) {
	const { factor } = units[i];

	units[i].usValue = +value;
	units[i].siValue = +(value * factor).toFixed(2);;
}
```

And then make sure to pass the index into those functions like this

```html
&lt;input value={usValue} on:input=&quot;{e =&gt; setBothFromUS(e.target.value, i)}&quot; min=&quot;&quot; type=number placeholder=&quot; US&quot;&gt;
```

