I have found a work-around solution for your problem. So, the basic idea is this:

Place a `WebView` behind everything in the opening screen of your app(So that it is hidden). Place a blank php file in your domain. Access this php file from this `WebView`. Accept the cookie which will be sent from the server and store it in `SharedPreferences`. You can use this cookie in the rest of your app as this cookie is newly created.

**My example code:-**

Sample.php:

    &lt;?php
    ?&gt;
Store the cookie using `WebView` and `CookieManager` in `MainActivity` of your app:

    String url=&quot;http://your_domain.com/Sample.php&quot;;
    
    CookieSyncManager.createInstance(mContext);
            cookieManager=CookieManager.getInstance();
            webView.getSettings().setJavaScriptEnabled(true);
    
            webView.setWebViewClient(new WebViewClient(){
    
                @Override
                public void onPageFinished(WebView view, String url) {
                    super.onPageFinished(view, url);
    
                    cookieManager.setAcceptCookie(true);
                    cookie=cookieManager.getCookie(url);
    
                    System.out.println(cookie);
    
                    SharedPreferences sharedPreferences=getSharedPreferences(&quot;CookieDetails&quot;,MODE_PRIVATE);
                    SharedPreferences.Editor editor=sharedPreferences.edit();
                    editor.putString(&quot;cookieStart&quot;,cookie);
                    editor.apply();
                 
                    //YOU CAN USE THE COOKIE AFTER THIS
    
                }
            });
    
            webView.setWebChromeClient(new WebChromeClient());
            webView.loadUrl(url);
    
    
    
            webView.clearCache(true);
            webView.clearHistory();
    
            cookieManager.removeAllCookie();
            cookieManager.removeSessionCookie();

Override the `getHeaders()` method in your `StringRequest` class like this:

    @Override
        public Map&lt;String, String&gt; getHeaders() throws AuthFailureError
        {
            Map&lt;String,String&gt; headers=new HashMap&lt;&gt;();
            SharedPreferences sharedPreferences=mContext.getSharedPreferences(&quot;CookieDetails&quot;,Context.MODE_PRIVATE);
            String cookieStart=sharedPreferences.getString(&quot;cookieStart&quot;,&quot;&quot;);
    
            headers.put(&quot;Cookie&quot;,cookieStart+&quot;; expires=Friday, 1 January 2038 at 05:25:55; path=/&quot;);
    
            return headers;
        }

After this you can make volley GET and POST request like you do usually. 

Cheers!

